    "description": "The first light of dawn catches the white lighthouse at Cape Byron, Australia's easternmost point, as pods of dolphins ride the waves below. The scent of salt and eucalyptus fills the air, mixing with the aroma of fresh coffee from beachside cafes where surfers check the swell reports. The town's rhythm is set by the tides - morning yoga on the beach gives way to surf sessions at The Pass, while in the afternoon, the streets fill with the sound of didgeridoos and the chatter of market vendors selling organic produce. As the sun sets over the hinterland, the night comes alive with the sound of live music from hidden venues, where the scent of patchouli mingles with the sea breeze. Byron's magic lies in this perfect balance of natural beauty and alternative culture, where every day feels like a celebration of the good life.",
